    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5748.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 118.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose a copy of a letter from A. A. Lisman
                    &amp; Co., of New York, inquiring what has become of the issues of certain bonds
                    of the Entre Rios Eastern Railway Company described therein.</p>
                <p>You will endeavor to secure the information desired and transmit it to the
                    department for communication to Messrs. Lisman &amp; Co.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lisman</persName> to the <gloss
                                type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-05">
                                <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1907</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Clients of ours are holders of the Entre Rios
                        Eastern Railway Company 6 per cent gold-coin bonds, which bear the following
                        indorsement:</p>
                    <p>“This bond is secured by a guarantee made by the Argentine Republic of an
                        income to the company of 7 per cent per annum upon the entire issue of its
                        first-mortgage bonds for twenty years, which is pledged to the holder hereof
                        for the payment of its interest and sinking fund.”</p>
                    <p>Would it be possible for your department to ascertain what has become of the
                        issues of the security above named?</p>
                    <p>The company issuing these bonds was a Massachusetts corporation formed in
                        1881.</p>
                    <p>Very respectfully, yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. A. Lisman</hi> &amp; Co.</closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
